txt.en:
'Misery me, [placeholder]! I've heard those quiet, little mews around Wistmead again.

'I have enough to manage already looking after all this!'

Iris gestures to the cats at her feet and more subtly towards Walaric.

'In time, I will be glad to see them off to Bree, but for now, it seems the festival-goers have grown fond of them! Would you go and find a few more of those black cats for me?'
Talk to Iris Tunnelly in Wistmead
Iris Tunnelly can be found in Wistmead.\n\nYou have found several black cats for Iris Tunnelly, and you should now bring them to her in Wistmead.
Found black cats for Iris Tunnelly in Wistmead ([placeholder]/[placeholder])

'Good gracious!

'As much as I enjoy having them around for the Harvest Festival, it will be a great relief when this is all over! Once I get back to Staddle, that woman from Bree can have the lot of them!

'O! But... perhaps I'll ask to keep one for myself!'
Find black cats for Iris Tunnelly in Wistmead ([placeholder]/[placeholder])

Black cats can be found throughout Wistmead.\n\nIris Tunnelly has asked you to aid her in gathering a number of black cats in Wistmead that they might bring joy to festival-goers and eventually find a new home in Bree-town.
Much to the amusement of its patrons, a number of black cats have begun to appear at the Harvest Festival.
